        "client_msg_id": "0ac1ded5-4dee-4d0b-aa00-857f625cd28e",
        "type": "message",
        "text": "Yes, Sketch.systems is an interesting project. I was also closely following <https:\/\/subformapp.com\/|Subform> (made by the same people) while it was in development. Part of what I think is needed is the ability for both designers and developers to work in a sort of “UI only” mode where the business logic is simulated (faked really) and the data is pre-built samples. There is a lot of power in being able to easily put your UI into an interesting state or to simulate error conditions, empty states, slow network calls, etc. Or to just be free of having to set up and run all that code! I think a tool that lets you simulate the logic of an application for those purposes might look something like Sketch.systems",
