        "type": "message",
        "text": "By 2) I mean, UI testing is pretty flaky these days, with frameworks that do things like scraping HTML looking for things with given classes or IDs to click them. I think it wouldn't be too hard to come up with that metadata in a format usable for automating. A screen reader could use that info too. And it could be used as a tool to trim the state-space as much as possible. So I think of these tings as closely related.",
