        "type": "message",
        "text": "Totally agree. In my experience many accessibility issues are raised by developers because they are the only ones really working in the medium. It’s the sort of thing that should be the domain of the designer in my opinion (although why not both!) There are similar issues with responsive design, using real data, etc. I’ve been imagining integrating into existing frameworks for building UIs, so it would be a matter of making sure that the building block components are built to support accessibility and UI testing.",
